My instruments are all built by hand, by me, in my shop.  I make guitars like the old-world craftsman; I do it all myself and each step is painstakingly performed with precision and detail.
<br><br>
I have been a guitar player for 42 years and I taught guitar for 20 years (although I no longer have time).  I built my first guitar in my father's woodworking shop at age 13 (it was a solidbody electric that I've unfortunately misplaced after moving over ten times over the years).  After high school I apprenticed for a master luthier in New Jersey for about five years.
